I've read the thread here, the thread on XA boards and the thread on HKD boards.  The only reason I feel I should voice yet another opinion on this topic is because I am part of HKD.<br>
<br>
Here is the main problem as I see it - HKD, XA leaders are all at fault in this mess.  Slyde should have gathered more information and taken this issue to a more private venue before opening it up to public shredding.  <br>
<br>
XA leaders are at fault for miscommunication to the raid that was ending. (ie not everyone on the raid was in the XA chat and information was passed to there, not the raid channel.  A forgivable and very easy to make mistake.)  <br>
<br>
Delt did recieve &quot;insider information&quot; and used that for his gain.  Is it right, is it wrong?  Well, if you took it to court and this were the financial world he'd be in a heap of trouble.  But this is EQ folks, kudos to him on being out there working hard to be privy to this information.  If I, or Rukog were in his shoes, we would never have asked for a default to ourselves.  Delt didn't have to open roll on it, that is a call only each individual could make.  In HKD we pride ourselves and reward selflessness, therefore it's hard for some of us to understand how anyone in that situation could seperate the end of an XA raid and a single guild coming in and allowing those raiders to attend without being allowed to roll on a hard to get epic piece.  Soul Survivors had no obligations to those raiders once they took over.<br>
<br>
In all these threads there are only 2 side issues that I must debate.<br>
<br>
****quote***I'm in full belief that if House Kel'Dar, or whatever their name is now, cared about their mage, they would have been there too had they known he was up; I would garner he would have told his guild he wanted this piece, and them knowing he was in hate, they might have had their ears pricked up to assist him or congrat him. I find it hard to believe that in all this time the Magi was up, this mage who was waiting and hoping and praying for him to spawn, and was on this raid to benefit himself in a way his guild would apparently not, had never once seen him cast a spell. The very minute I entered the plane and went to the camp spot I could see the Magi Casting.***end quote***<br>
<br>
If you already had forces gathering as soon as everyone says here, HKD never would have considered going for Magi.   Are you suggesting that HKD should have tried to leapfrog your guild into Fear to get Magi for Fenren?  And if Fenren had asked, which he didn't, that would have been pointed out to him.  I think he knew better than to ask us to try to rush ahead of you all to get him the piece.  As for not noticing him up, well I have npc spells off if I'm on any character other than my enchanter.<br>
<br>
The other side topic I want to point out is to Strad or however you spell his name.  That vox or naggy raid, shesh get over it already.  Those 55+ players were there the whole raid, buffed the 55- characters and helped them to get the dragon.  They were there for teleports, tps, rezes and buffs after the raid.  The exception of them being in on the lottos was announced and agreed on by all.  They did just as much work to get to the mob and make killing the mob a success as did the -55 players.  Yes, I was there.<br>
<br>
Last but not least, I have learned one thing in this whole mess....  I like Ketal!!!  She's just the bees knees!<br>
