I scrolled up my chat window and found someone in SRo who was not likely to be too involved in buffing - a warrior.  I sent a /tell asking for the name of a SS officer and was told, word for word, "#### off."  I put this marvel of intelligent conversation on /ignore and sent two other /tells to randomly selected people in the zone; one didn't reply at all, the other said "we don't have officers."  A guild without officers - how novel.  At this point I decided that further attempts to have a meaningful dialogue with SS was unlikely to bear fruit and contacted Slyde.<br>
<br>
So, Deltamamos - assuming you read this - you just called ME a liar.  Directly.  After my run-ins with you when we were both in our mid-teens, I can't say I'm surprised - the quiet enchanter off to one side may not have made an impression on you, but I assure you that you surely made an impression on me.  But I don't have anything to prove to you; if the gods are kind, I don't have to have anything to do with you unless I have the ill luck to be traveling through the Nexus at the same time.  <br>
